## Threat Intelligence Platform (TIP) Architecture: A Comprehensive Summary
A TIP centralizes, analyzes, and operationalizes threat intelligence. Key terms: Threat Intelligence (info on threats, actors, TTPs, IoCs); TIP (automates collection-analysis-dissemination); IoCs (e.g., IPs, hashes); TTPs (MITRE ATT&amp;CK); Threat Data (raw) vs Intelligence (actionable).
**Threat Intelligence Lifecycle (6 Steps, TIP-Aligned):**
1. Requirements: Define needs (e.g., actor profiling).
2. Collection: OSINT, feeds, logs via TIP ingestion.
3. Processing: Normalize, deduplicate.
4. Analysis: Enrich (geolocation), correlate (ML/AI), detect patterns.
5. Production/Dissemination: Reports, dashboards, APIs (TAXII/STIX 2.1), integrate with tools.
6. Feedback: Refine based on efficacy.
**TIP Architecture:** Ingestion (connectors), Processing (parsers), Storage (Elasticsearch/Neo4j graph DBs), Analytics (rules/ML), Dissemination (UI/APIs). Standards: STIX 2.1, TAXII 2.1, MISP. Integrations: MITRE ATT&amp;CK, SIEM.
